documentation.text:
@title Long Short Pair.
 @notice Uses a combination of long and short tokens to tokenize the bounded price exposure to a given identifier.

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (bytes memory,address) view external returns (bytes memory)

documentation.text:
@notice Construct the LongShortPair
 @param params Constructor params used to initialize the LSP. Key-valued object with the following structure:
    pairName: Name of the long short pair contract.
    expirationTimestamp: Unix timestamp of when the contract will expire.
    collateralPerPair: How many units of collateral are required to mint one pair of synthetic tokens.
    priceIdentifier: Price identifier, registered in the DVM for the long short pair.
    longToken: Token used as long in the LSP. Mint and burn rights needed by this contract.
    shortToken: Token used as short in the LSP. Mint and burn rights needed by this contract.
    collateralToken: Collateral token used to back LSP synthetics.
    financialProductLibrary: Contract providing settlement payout logic.
    customAncillaryData: Custom ancillary data to be passed along with the price request to the OO.
    prepaidProposerReward: Preloaded reward to incentivize settlement price proposals.
    optimisticOracleLivenessTime: OO liveness time for price requests.
    optimisticOracleProposerBond: OO proposer bond for price requests.
    finder: DVM finder to find other UMA ecosystem contracts.
    timerAddress: Timer used to synchronize contract time in testing. Set to 0x000... in production.

params.params: Constructor params used to initialize the LSP. Key-valued object with the following structure:    pairName: Name of the long short pair contract.    expirationTimestamp: Unix timestamp of when the contract will expire.    collateralPerPair: How many units of collateral are required to mint one pair of synthetic tokens.    priceIdentifier: Price identifier, registered in the DVM for the long short pair.    longToken: Token used as long in the LSP. create(uint256).details: The caller must approve this contract to transfer `tokensToCreate * collateralPerPair` amount of collateral.

params.tokensToCreate: number of long and short synthetic tokens to create.

returns.collateralUsed: total collateral used to mint the synthetics.

returns._0: uint for the current Testable timestamp.

params.sponsor: address of the sponsor to query.

returns._0: [uint256, uint256]. First is long tokens held by sponsor and second is short tokens held by sponsor.

redeem(uint256).details: This contract must have the `Burner` role for the `longToken` and `shortToken` in order to call `burnFrom`.The caller does not need to approve this contract to transfer any amount of `tokensToRedeem` since long and short tokens are burned, rather than transferred, from the caller.

params.tokensToRedeem: number of long and short synthetic tokens to redeem.

returns.collateralReturned: total collateral returned in exchange for the pair of synthetics.

setCurrentTime(uint256).details: Will revert if not running in test mode.

params.time: timestamp to set current Testable time to.

settle(uint256,uint256).details: Uses financialProductLibrary to compute the redemption rate between long and short tokens.This contract must have the `Burner` role for the `longToken` and `shortToken` in order to call `burnFrom`.The caller does not need to approve this contract to transfer any amount of `tokensToRedeem` since long and short tokens are burned, rather than transferred, from the caller.

params.longTokensToRedeem: number of long tokens to settle.
params.shortTokensToRedeem: number of short tokens to settle.

returns.collateralReturned: total collateral returned in exchange for the pair of synthetics.

create(uint256).notice: Creates a pair of long and short tokens equal in number to tokensToCreate. Pulls the required collateral amount into this contract, defined by the collateralPerPair value.

getCurrentTime().notice: Gets the current time. Will return the last time set in `setCurrentTime` if running in test mode. Otherwise, it will return the block timestamp.

getPositionTokens(address).notice: Returns the number of long and short tokens a sponsor wallet holds.

redeem(uint256).notice: Redeems a pair of long and short tokens equal in number to tokensToRedeem. Returns the commensurate amount of collateral to the caller for the pair of tokens, defined by the collateralPerPair value.

settle(uint256,uint256).notice: Settle long and/or short tokens in for collateral at a rate informed by the contract settlement.

userdoc.notice: Uses a combination of long and short tokens to tokenize the bounded price exposure to a given identifier.
